/-! ## Achieved direct primitive proof-theoretic Hopf theorem -/

/--
The unconditional theorem currently achieved by the project.

This is deliberately weaker than `ProofTheoreticHopfMainResult`: it does not
claim the full OG antipode or global bialgebra laws.  Instead it records the
three pieces that are now proved uniformly for every material base relation:

* CK admissible-cut/graft reconstruction duality;
* nonmonotonic structural-rule diagnostics for weakening and grafting;
* the direct base-indexed OG primitive UEA theorem on derivable proof trees.

This is the clean "what we have" theorem for the proof-theoretic Hopf program.
-/
def DirectProofTheoreticHopfPrimitiveMainResult
    (base : BaseRel) : Prop :=
  CutGraftDualityMarqueeTarget
      base CKGraftReconstructionMultiplicity ∧
    NonmonotonicWeakeningGraftingMarquee base ∧
    DirectDerivableUEAOudomGuinPrimitiveTheorem base

